sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as maas-default-gateway<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant PreAuth as payload-processing<br/>(Pre-Auth)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Authorino as Authorino<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS
    participant MaaSAPI as maas-api<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant PostAuth as payload-processing<br/>(Post-Auth)<br/>9004/TCP gRPC TLS
    participant Backend as Model Backend<br/>(KServe/External)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant PostgreSQL as PostgreSQL<br/>5432/TCP TLS
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS

    rect rgb(240, 248, 255)
        Note over Client,Backend: Flow 1: Model Inference (OpenShift Token)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (OpenShift)
        Gateway->>PreAuth: ext_proc: Extract model name<br/>→ X-Gateway-Model-Name header
        PreAuth-->>Gateway: Model name extracted
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation<br/>Bearer token + model name
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select<br/>(NetworkPolicy-protected)
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Subscription selected<br/>X-Maas-Subscription header
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + identity headers<br/>X-MaaS-Username/Group/Tenant
        Gateway->>PostAuth: ext_proc: Provider resolution<br/>API translation + key injection
        PostAuth-->>Gateway: Request transformed
        Gateway->>Backend: Inference request<br/>Subscription-injected credentials
        Backend-->>Gateway: Prediction result
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(255, 248, 240)
        Note over Client,Backend: Flow 2: Model Inference (API Key)
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/models/model:predict<br/>Auth: X-Api-Key header
        Gateway->>PreAuth: ext_proc: Extract model name
        PreAuth-->>Gateway: Model name extracted
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation<br/>X-Api-Key header
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/api-keys/validate<br/>SHA-256 hash lookup
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: Query API key by hash<br/>(key_id + null byte + secret)
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key record + subscription
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Key valid + identity
        Authorino->>MaaSAPI: POST /internal/v1/subscriptions/select
        MaaSAPI-->>Authorino: Subscription selected
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + headers
        Gateway->>PostAuth: ext_proc: Provider resolution<br/>API translation + key injection
        PostAuth-->>Gateway: Request transformed
        Gateway->>Backend: Inference request
        Backend-->>Gateway: Prediction result
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end

    rect rgb(240, 255, 240)
        Note over Client,PostgreSQL: Flow 3: API Key Management
        Client->>Gateway: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>Auth: Bearer Token / OIDC JWT
        Gateway->>Authorino: AuthPolicy evaluation
        Authorino-->>Gateway: Auth OK + X-MaaS-* headers
        Gateway->>MaaSAPI: POST /v1/api-keys<br/>User identity via headers
        MaaSAPI->>K8sAPI: SubjectAccessReview<br/>(admin check, cached)
        K8sAPI-->>MaaSAPI: SAR result
        MaaSAPI->>PostgreSQL: INSERT API key<br/>(SHA-256 hash, tenant-scoped)
        PostgreSQL-->>MaaSAPI: Key created
        MaaSAPI-->>Gateway: API key response<br/>(key shown once)
        Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response
    end
